result.name: Chinese Kitchen

reviews.text:
Damn! If only I took a look on the internet first about this restaurant. 

I ate there because they served vegetarian food. Service was bad NOT FRIENDLY. The taste of milk tea? Never ever try it, awful. And what?? I found something like hair in my food and I paid too much for this they called "food"!!

They should close this place so soon!

Not surprised by reviews. 1 star is too many. Should be 0. Ordered 北京炸醬麵 and some of noodles was hard. No taste. Boiled pork or beef tossed on top. Adding chilli oil couldn't even help. Girlfriend got chicken and rice. Rice came on the side and didn't taste fresh. Like they made it in the morning and sat for so many hours. Chicken was 2 - 3 pieces with a LOT of garlic to hide it and peppers and onions. On top of that bill was way too high. You can find high quality HK cusine in downtown for half the price... sigh. 

Hope customers review this place before deciding to eat!

They served raw pork dumplings to my little one.He ate two out of four when we released that its  raw and the staffs also admitted. 

I was shocked how come they serve these kind of raw food to kids.. are they blind or too much busy chit chatting..
bad serves, expensive foods tea and serves
too expensive

result.name: Hong Kong International Airport North Satellite Concourse

reviews.text: Separate terminal from main terminal, but very near shuttle buses available every 4 mins. 10 gates which mainly cater for dragon air. Few shops like electronics,  coffee shop,  restaurant each one available. Less crowd but can view the sea from here.

There are only 10 gates, as far as I remember, and there is not even one drink vending machine at this concourse. Since this concourse is quite small, here is only limited food is available. Instead, there is a smoking area near the men's washroom.
Крутой аэропорт, влюбилась. Буду всегда летать через него
